<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
  <head>
 
  </head>
  <body>
    <% if logged_in? %>
      <div id="center" class="uk-container">
        <div  class="uk-height-medium uk-flex uk-flex-center uk-flex-middle uk-background-cover uk-secondary"
              data-src="../images/welcome2.jpg"
              data-sizes="(min-width: 650px) 650px, 100vw" uk-img>
          <ul></br></br><br>
        <p>
          <h1>Welcome, <%= @user.first_name %></h1>
        </p>
        <% if @user.course_id.to_i > 0 %>
          <p>You are in course: <%= @user.course.name %></p>
        <% else %>
          <p>You haven't assigned course yet.</p>
          <p><a class="uk-button uk-button-default" href="#modal-overflow" uk-toggle>Take a test here!</a></p>
          <div id="modal-overflow" uk-modal>
            <div class="uk-modal-dialog">
              <button class="uk-modal-close-default" type="button" uk-close></button>
              <div class="uk-modal-header">
                <h2 class="uk-modal-title">English Placement Test</h2>
                If you are a new student at SPACELESSS, you will need to take the English placement tests before you begin classes. The results of these tests will help you and SPACELESS determine the courses you will take
              </div>
              <div class="uk-modal-body" uk-overflow-auto>
                <ul>Read the statement or passage. Choose the best answer to the question. Answer the question on the basis of what is stated or implied in the statement or passage.</ul>
                <ul>Myths are stories, the product of fertile imaginations, sometimes simple, often containing profound truths. They are not meant to be taken too literally. Details may sometimes appear childish, but most myths express a culture's most serious beliefs about human beings, eternity, and God.</ul>
                <ul>The main idea of this passage is that myths</br></br>
              <li>A. are created primarily to entertain young children.</li>
              <li>B. are purposely written for the reader who lacks imagination.</li>
              <li>C. provide the reader with a means of escape from reality</li>
              <li>D. illustrate the values that are considered important to a society.</li>
              <p>This's an example of placement tests. </p>
              <p>Click Submit to random select your course! </p>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <form method="POST" action="/random/<%= @user.id %>">
            <div class="uk-modal-footer uk-text-right">
              <input type="hidden" name="_method" id="hidden" value="patch"/>
              <button class="uk-button uk-button-primary"  type="submit">Submit</button>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %></br>
</ul>
</div>
<br>
<div id="center" class="uk-section uk-light bg"  style="height: 200px">
  <% if @user.course_id.to_i > 0 %>
    <p>You have <%= @user.course.assignments.where(status: true).size - @user.user_assignments.where(status: true).size %> assignment(s) on process </p>
    <p><a href="/assignments"><button class="uk-button uk-button-default">Submit Assignment</button></a></p>
  <% else %>
    <p>You have no assignment yet.</a></p>
<% end %>
</div>
</br>
<div id="center" class="uk-section uk-light bg"  style="height: 200px">
  <% if @user.course_id.to_i > 0 %>
    <p>Let's join in our community! </p>
    <p> <a href="/posts"><button class="uk-button uk-button-default">GO</button></a></p>
  <% else %>
    <p>You have no group yet.</a></p>
<% end %>
</div>
</br>
</div>
<% else %>
  <a href="/signup">Sign Up</a>
  <a href="/login"> Sign In </a>
<%end %>
</body>
</html>
